        "cmip6.seaice.thermodynamics.mass.new_ice_formation": {
            "values": [
                "Sea ice is formed when sea surface temperature (temperature of the top layer of the ocean model) is below freezing point. The heat needed to raise the temperature to the freezing point is regarded as the latent heat release through the sea ice formation."
